Product Requirements Document (PRD) - Clinical Hub & FHIR AI Agent
1. Executive Summary
The Clinical Hub is a modern, high-performance web application designed for clinicians to interact with FHIR-based medical data. It combines traditional data visualization (Dashboards, Timelines) with advanced AI capabilities (Causal Analysis, Agentic Drafting) to streamline clinical workflows and improve decision-making.

2. Platform Objectives
Centralize Clinical Data: Provide a single pane of glass for Encounters, Observations, Vitals, Conditions, and Procedures.
Enhance Data Entry: Use AI-driven agents to simplify the creation of FHIR resources.
Maintain Data Integrity: Provide robust CRUD operations for patient demographics and clinical statuses.
Optimize Performance: Use virtualization (via virtua) to handle large clinical datasets without UI lag.
3. Key Feature Modules
3.1 Patient Dashboard
Overview: A high-level summary of a patient's current state.
Metrics: Real-time display of critical vitals and condition severity.
Timeline: A chronological visualization of the clinical journey (Vis-Timeline integration).
3.2 Patient Demographics CRUD
Compact Header: Immediate access to MRN, Name, Gender, Age, and Code Status.
Management Modal: Full access to identifiable data, contacts, and care team.
Persistence: Direct synchronization with FHIR Patient and Observation resources.
3.3 AI Agent Integration
Capabilities:
Natural language querying of clinical records.
Automated drafting of clinical notes/resources.
Causal analysis of longitudinal data (e.g., identifying drivers for condition changes).
Models Supported: Google Gemini (1.5 Pro/Flash), Groq-hosted models.
3.4 Clinical Document Management
Viewer: High-fidelity viewing of diagnostic reports and clinical documents.
Creation: Specialized modals for adding new Encounters, Conditions, and Observations.
4. Technical Architecture
Frontend: Next.js 13+ (App Router), React 18.
Styling: Tailwind CSS with "Glassmorphism" aesthetic and full Dark Mode support.
State Management: Server-side fetching with client-side React hooks for real-time interactivity.
Backend API: Next.js API Routes orchestrating FHIR Server communication.
Invariants:
Full TypeScript type safety for FHIR R4 resources.
Virtualized lists for scalability.
5. Deployment & Infrastructure
Authentication: iron-session based session management.
Security: HIPAA-compliant data handling (no local storage of PHI).
Integration: Supports any standard FHIR R4 server endpoint (Epic, Cerner, HAPI, etc.).
6. Roadmap
V1.1: Enhanced AI Causal Analysis UI.
V1.2: Direct PDF generation for clinical summaries.
V2.0: Multi-patient population health views.
7. Success Metrics
Clinician Efficiency: Time reduction in demographic updates and data lookup.
Accuracy: 100% fidelity in FHIR resource mapping.
System Load: Zero UI jank on lists exceeding 1000+ observations.